<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-DBF33922-83C6-48F8-BA00-B57292FE9A6A" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-DBF33922-83C6-48F8-BA00-B57292FE9A6A" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Load a media roll (position 1)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-7C628825-B6E1-4DE5-ACF8-0E4206424F0A"><p class="- topic/p "><ph class="- topic/ph "><indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">Load a media roll</indexterm><indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">Media loading</indexterm></ph> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This topic describes how to load a media roll in position 1. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-C8AF9162-777C-40E3-B782-46A5BB2F88A2"><p class="- topic/p ">You can use an optional grip lock to insert the feed media shaft into the core of the new media roll. You can load a media roll without the optional grip lock. This procedure describes both situations. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-B522A4DF-3694-45DB-ACDA-E5FD363C1ACF" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p ">Before you load a roll on the printer: 
</p><ul id="UL_FD9235B8864447D0B315B5DC9B077AD5" class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you have added a media profile with the correct media type via the RIP. 
</p></li><li id="LI_C992D019CA154A09B5A4DBCB37C4C680" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the media width of your roll before loading. When your media width is not present in the list on the operator panel, you can type it in. 
</p></li><li id="LI_10B80273AF5F4D7FB16FA0D0E76CD3D6" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Put on gloves to avoid pollution of the paper by your fingerprints. 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-B2A258B3-B440-48E0-A0C5-B596C42E0741" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="GUID-174B62E7-08A5-4754-9F7A-37F20358FA48" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><ul id="d448e113" class="- topic/ul "><li id="d448e114" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Watch your fingers when you handle the media roll. 
</p></li><li id="d448e117" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Loading heavy media, 25 kg (55 lb) or more, has to be done by two people or with the help of external lifting tools. 
</p></li></ul></note><note id="GUID-634FAFF5-0B56-4DEB-A5E0-F28D9C929250" class="- topic/note " type="important"><ul id="d448e66" class="- topic/ul "><li id="d448e67" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not use dented or damaged media rolls to prevent damage to the printheads. 
</p></li><li id="d448e70" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Only open the media drawer when the indicator light on the drawer is on. Do not open the drawer when the light is off, you can damage the machine. 
</p></li></ul></note></section><steps id="GUID-A44C0E06-DC76-48B6-9CA1-C75A581BA9C6" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_E73C3E50B2994C80A466C1642FF58A1C" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Pull firmly to open the media drawer. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_14C6EAC3D650477BBB0A215E57E9A1AB" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Place the new media roll, with the media flap on the bottom and towards you, on the roll loading station. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_ED7516B418BA4E079BB4E4C5841947F5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7BA57E0D-E7F5-43B0-893D-219D2E12E755-low.png" id="IMAGE_125CC11D0A1E454189BE46DDC1E1BB87" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7BA57E0D-E7F5-43B0-893D-219D2E12E755-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_2838A2E9DF4B4290AC0CC5FDA9D84C35" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Pull the lever and open the clamp. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_BA173712F75D4435BF42A99A7D0D3D8B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6CC9AFC4-9F03-4226-B822-327BE403EFC8-low.png" id="IMAGE_6D0BC93C6B9649ABA67B5EB923A90357" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6CC9AFC4-9F03-4226-B822-327BE403EFC8-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_E17C60AFA15747C3A2A4F1C5E2400A65" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take the feed media shaft out of the drawer. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_3093C901844C4889BCD2DFB326F29AC7" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Insert the feed media shaft into the core of the new media roll. You can use the optional grip lock for this step. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">With the optional grip lock: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Pull (1) the handle of the locking mechanism towards you. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the grip lock (2) in the feed media shaft. 
</p><fig id="GUID-D74FBB2E-CED7-4DCD-B0D1-73B8A97199AB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-56546564-B5D8-414D-9F4F-F379132DD4FD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-56546564-B5D8-414D-9F4F-F379132DD4FD-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide (3) the media shaft into the side of the core of the new media roll. 
</p><fig id="GUID-50493E9E-45CE-412E-998B-DDBCCD1CB3E0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A718640B-0889-4B08-8FDC-E044478E5355-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A718640B-0889-4B08-8FDC-E044478E5355-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the grip lock. 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p ">Without the optional grip lock: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Pull (1) the handle of the locking mechanism towards you. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide (2) the media shaft into the side of the core of the new media roll. 
</p><fig outputclass="photo" id="M143306-F490" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EB2AD7C6-2E89-4AC0-8325-0E18C50F528A-low.png" id="IMAGE_F13E34FD0D12428EAF384B542A7B1D64" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EB2AD7C6-2E89-4AC0-8325-0E18C50F528A-low.png"/></fig></li></ol></info></step><step id="STEP_9EEC2B96611D47E99E8D1EEDE7DFE9D9" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Accurately align the roll on the media shaft. Place it on the corresponding media size with the help of the ruler. Check on the left and right side of the roll if both are aligned on the same size. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig outputclass="photo" id="M143306-F492" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EF5A04A8-8364-42FD-BEEB-54451F3C6363-low.png" id="IMAGE_39CA6385B7124B68AC6D7060907662A5" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EF5A04A8-8364-42FD-BEEB-54451F3C6363-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_F6DA8B79B464475E80D2EBD3EC648D45" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Release the handle of the locking mechanism. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_32F4DD6C339440D38A0D8BDF28F133A4" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the tapes from the new media roll, if present. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the media roll in the media drawer. 
</p><fig outputclass="photo" id="M143306-F495" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2EFF3698-8D0B-4C17-8A57-B3FB2DB7753C-low.png" id="IMAGE_5A5D4F9125124A4B81078C769D0C4E71" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2EFF3698-8D0B-4C17-8A57-B3FB2DB7753C-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_43E1D3F46D6B474F9D705D4B63B41505" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the clamp firmly. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-F97FF9B4-ED46-4975-B2EC-FFF8E03E1E42" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you close the clamp completely until you hear a click, otherwise the roll can come loose and can damage the machine. 
</p></note></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_1A1B0EECC8D44376B252D6070CCC941C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DC74D7C7-7DB3-4C1D-B2C4-50CD9387CFD3-low.png" id="IMAGE_9A399386CB284AE58DD47B847CF3E83A" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DC74D7C7-7DB3-4C1D-B2C4-50CD9387CFD3-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_B2B9FE3A7C00454C81B555D1DFA7698F" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Use both hands to turn the media roll backwards (1) until the media flap has passed the metal paper guide. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig outputclass="photo" id="M143306-F497" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-23995ABC-8F95-4B70-B113-F2DF2805A0B8-low.png" id="IMAGE_DF6BC5E0892B4277A39FB419A2524EA0" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-23995ABC-8F95-4B70-B113-F2DF2805A0B8-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_63A5259D2DB54072AC315761F80E0D54" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Use both hands to move the media forward and slide it under the metal paper guide (2) until the media is transported automatically. You will hear a beeping sound when the media is correctly fed and loaded. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-9D69BBC8-6135-41E5-AEB9-E6159AB10D02" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure media is always rolled up evenly on the core. Do not load media that is not rolled up evenly (telescoping) as it can damage the machine. 
</p></note></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig outputclass="photo" id="M143306-F499" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B4002A45-943C-4CEB-845C-02279D527F40-low.png" id="IMAGE_88F608793D8E4450A78D66C7021553AA" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B4002A45-943C-4CEB-845C-02279D527F40-low.png"/></fig></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">When the printer does not take the media (no beeping sound), you can feed the media manually. The manual feeding option is recommended for flexible and difficult to load media, such as canvas and textiles. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For manual feeding: 
</p></info><substeps id="SUBSTEPS_4894696A8141483DA896DBF5730611DD" class="- topic/ol task/substeps "><substep id="SUBSTEP_6FC80E58B2E14E419A7127C03C3F93D1" class="- topic/li task/substep "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Push the handles on the left and right side of the loading station to open the media feed. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_416BCACF9ED74ED5A6B31F714CB58ABD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-502BC233-123C-4C8C-A6EC-15E08CD7A078-low.png" id="IMAGE_C0FEA48CB9824868A8BC3FF23E5CF07D" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-502BC233-123C-4C8C-A6EC-15E08CD7A078-low.png"/></fig></info></substep><substep id="SUBSTEP_D3A89E896BCA4FDD93C2B8323F80DDC7" class="- topic/li task/substep "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Use both hands to move the media forward and slide the media under the metal paper guide until you see it coming out on top. 
</cmd></substep><substep id="SUBSTEP_104F9EB90DED4AD990ED449E2EE90150" class="- topic/li task/substep "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the media feed. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_D1DE5C8EFF2C453191536FF8DCE244F9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DF5A0A13-A652-4ACC-BA86-F2231F0D2BC6-low.png" id="IMAGE_2CA524412BF849C8947D13C1617DB531" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DF5A0A13-A652-4ACC-BA86-F2231F0D2BC6-low.png"/></fig></info></substep><substep id="SUBSTEP_E766827EB99F4D2C8BE1A5A89F022AF8" class="- topic/li task/substep "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If necessary, you can manually cut the leading edge of the media when it has not been cut straight. Take a knife and cut the media in the cutting guide. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note type="note" id="GUID-69A41985-A23C-41F1-8163-7AAF658C7181" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Always use a straight cut leading edge for media types that are more difficult to transport (e.g. canvas). 
</p></note></info></substep></substeps></step><step id="STEP_4517586125214DAAAB99EFB0D7F1D6BC" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the media drawer carefully. The operator panel displays the message that new media is detected. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-6F1ADE58-FB07-4CE2-9E5F-92DA7712B692" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">Do not open the media drawer when the indicator light is off, you can damage the machine. 
</p></note></info></step><step id="STEP_D5C223978396448889CC4B6F55993D92" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel, select the correct media type and fill in the media width. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_F25E74210D57457283D7901E5E34A039" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-18318CC5-95A5-4147-BB99-02B32B1B1374-low.png" id="IMAGE_CD3BD43F55B84641BF6A197214B5E6B2" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-18318CC5-95A5-4147-BB99-02B32B1B1374-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">When the media you use has an upward curl select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text "> Upward curled media</text></uicontrol>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p "> This setting persists as long as the media is assigned. When enabled, the system feeds the media to the output position. You can then open the top cover and guide the media. After you close the top cover, the media is transported to the clamp. Open the top cover and guide the media again. Printing starts after these actions have been completed. 
</p></info></step><step id="STEP_2443B5974EA9434CAF8BEC497C640C1A" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select if and what type of clean cut you want the printer to make, when you use the media for the first time. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">For winding with a tension bar or with a locked tension bar the clean cut is neglected. 
</p></info></step><step id="STEP_A441D626713B43598FB7290167EA6DFA" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Save</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-F8096ADC-1967-4FF5-8944-8F0C937AD250" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">For the highest output quality, it is advised to always perform a media calibration when you load a new media type or a new media width. 
</p></note></info></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5B8E84B8-092A-4B76-84E3-AA295749E97E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
